Author: _jonathan3
Content:
Dampak dan Implikasi Revisi RUU TNI
Perubahan dalam RUU TNI 2025 ini menimbulkan berbagai dampak, baik dalam aspek pemerintahan, keamanan, maupun keseimbangan peran sipil dan militer:

Perluasan Keterlibatan TNI di Sektor Sipil
Dengan bertambahnya institusi yang dapat diisi oleh prajurit TNI aktif, peran militer dalam pemerintahan semakin luas. Hal ini dianggap sebagai strategi untuk memperkuat koordinasi dalam bidang keamanan nasional serta kesiapsiagaan menghadapi ancaman seperti bencana dan terorisme.

Kekhawatiran terhadap Dwifungsi ABRI
Sejumlah pengamat, termasuk Peneliti Senior Imparsial Al Araf, menilai bahwa revisi ini berpotensi menghidupkan kembali konsep dwifungsi ABRI seperti pada era Orde Baru. Mereka mengingatkan bahwa tugas utama TNI adalah dalam sektor pertahanan, bukan dalam jabatan sipil yang dapat mengaburkan batas antara peran militer dan pemerintahan.

Pentingnya Penguatan Pengawasan Publik
Sebagian pihak berpendapat bahwa alih-alih memperluas peran TNI dalam jabatan sipil, yang lebih mendesak adalah meningkatkan sistem pengawasan publik. Hal ini diperlukan untuk memastikan transparansi dan akuntabilitas dalam kinerja institusi militer maupun pemerintahan.

Author: nick3512
Content:
Case study re debating different views

imo, the US is an "ideal" country bcs it's a country that was built from scratch and from the ground up. When the settlers (whose descendants later became the founding fathers) ran from England and landed on the new land, the settlers were on a mission and there was no debate on what this mission should be or about. 

They shared the same dream and aspiration for building a new nation and government based on what they hv been dreaming of and came to a consensus about what the ideal nation and government should look like (separation of church from state, check & balance of executive power, etc). 

We can see that US gov these days taken a completely hands-off approach when it comes to allowing society to debate among themselves as long as it doesn't evolve into physical violence. 

That said, the free-for-all debate in the US, imo, is being built upon the foundation (or context) where this country is being built upon a non-debate foundation while Indonesia and many other countries in the world didn't have the luxury of building a nation from scratch with a singular mission without any debate. Even today we, as Indonesians, have yet to come to a consensus as to what is it the nation that we aspire to and dream of. 

Therefore, while on principle, I 100% agree that we should not be worried about debating different views, at the same time, all these debates are not being debated upon the context of a certain foundation/mission that everyone aspired to fight for and therefore, a lot of times, all these debates in Indonesia end up to be a just an empty debate with no purpose imo.

Author: monke_eat_banana
Content:
Didn't the american dream become as successful because of WW2 and the Cold War? The US was struggling from the Great Depression, but WW2 provided the citizens with jobs (soldiers) and the constant external pressure forced the nation to cement its american dream. This continued even through the Cold War. There's always a looming threat that keep the american citizen to strive for their unified dream.
It only succeeds because there is a perceived crisis in the eyes of the people.

The same goes for China. The century of humiliation *was* a wide-spread crisis that lingered long enough that it rooted itself in the mindset of Chinese citizens.

I believe the key here is:
1. The same perception among the majority of citizens
2. That perception remained long enough that it successfully anchors itself into generations of people

I believe for Indonesia to be create its own "american dream", such a crisis must occur. I cannot see how a good vision from the president will be everlasting.
